Aedilibus Cur, These magistrates were entrusted with management of public games and theatrical representations; probably having like our Lord Chamberlain the authority to reject any play which they thought unfit for public performance. The decision of such a point they would relegate to some competent critic. Hence when Terence offered his Andria to them they referred him to Caecilius. Suetonius’ Life of Terence,
